# Presentation Content Quality

Applies to all content edits for this presentation repository.

## Slide content standards
- Keep bullets concise and scannable, usually one core idea per bullet.
- Prefer strong, concrete wording over vague abstractions.
- Maintain a clear narrative progression between neighboring slides.
- Preserve the existing bilingual style where Bulgarian and English technical terms are intentionally mixed.
- Avoid repeating the same claim across multiple bullets unless it is intentionally reframed.

## Tool capability truthfulness (very strict)
- Never invent or assume what a tool can do.
- Before claiming a capability, verify it from at least one reliable source in current context:
  - official documentation,
  - repository/project documentation,
  - explicitly provided source text.
- If capability is not verified, write it as unknown rather than guessing.
- Use explicit phrasing for uncertain claims:
  - "Unverified in current context: ..."
  - "Unknown without official/source confirmation."
- Do not present speculative capability statements as facts.

## Writing constraints
- Prefer actionable, audience-ready phrasing.
- Keep claims testable and specific.
- Remove hype language unless it serves a clear rhetorical purpose in the talk.
